STEP 1
- multisample anti-aliasing (SSAA, FSAA, MSAA, FXAA, MLAA, ...) see http://osghelp.com/?p=179  http://osghelp.com/?p=48   https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spatial_anti-aliasing
- motion blur (see http://forum.openscenegraph.org/viewtopic.php?t=12182)
- change the background color

STEP 2
- callbacks, osg basics, ...
- draw lines (e.g. to draw edges of 3D graphs from .dot files)     http://osghelp.com/?p=48  http://forum.openscenegraph.org/viewtopic.php?t=9658&view=previous  http://svn.openscenegraph.org/osg/OpenSceneGraph/tags/osg_v0_9_7_rc1_sync_release/examples/osggeometry/osggeometry.cpp   http://www.delta3d.org/forum/viewtopic.php?showtopic=16609
- Animation path (to smoothly move an object from point A to point B) see http://osghelp.com/?p=19 (useful for physics, 3D graphs animations, MCTS, ...)
- particles
- create objects form vertices, modify vertices of objects

STEP 3
- light / shadow
- colors
- transparent objects
- mirror surfaces
- textures (http://osghelp.com/?p=119)

STEP 4
- OpenGL shaders (...) see http://trac.openscenegraph.org/projects/osg//wiki/Support/Tutorials/ShadersIntroduction
- post processing effects (depth of field, ...)
- soft shadows (radiosity), ...
- clouds (volumetric), volumetric textures, ...

- artistic stuff : e.g. see http://www.creativeapplications.net/c/openscenegraph-and-cefix-c-ipad/

See http://www.packtpub.com/openscenegrap-3-for-advanced-3d-programming-using-api-cookbook/book
